      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The long-term benefits of cleaner air and less gridlock are objectively massive, making the economic friction a necessary cost for a modern, sustainable city. Those who focus solely on the immediate cost are prioritizing short-term convenience over long-term public health and environmental stability. A functioning city requires prioritizing collective well-being over individual driving habits, and congestion pricing is the most direct way to enforce that necessary shift.",
